  poem:
    text: "Youth came to me, \r\nA lamentation of musk that  \r\nCould not be purchased
      even at a high price, \r\nAnd the scent of lavender \r\nIn the valleys of a
      meadow, \r\nAfter the pouring rain \n\nUbaid ibn al Abras "
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  contextInfos:
  - text: Lavender doesn't lose its scent. Even when cut or dried, the oil holds
      for years.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: Lavender oil is also used in many aromatheraphies, especially to calm nerves,
      and in medical anxiety Treatment
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: already in acient times it was know that lavender wine helpts to ease "pains
      of the side and the nerves, and extreme cold." (De Matedia medica - Dioscorides)
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: the Name stems fron Latin "lavare" - washing. Romains laid it in Baths,
      beds and linen.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: To "lay up in lavender" is to fold a thing away wrapped in the herb, safe
      from moths and time.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: "Lavender - Alfred Noyes (excerpt)\nLavender, lavender, \nFrom where the
      bee hums, \nTo the loud roar of London,\nWith purple dreams he comes, \nFrom
      ragged lanes of wild-Flowers\nTo ragged London slums, \nWith a basket full
      of lavender \nAnd purple dreams he comes."
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
